Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.22,0:00:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Blood pressure, 120 over 80;\Npulse, 92.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.78,0:00:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I will now remove the bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.71,0:00:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I have removed the bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.76,0:00:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The removal is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.56,0:00:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little early to be relieved;
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.06,0:00:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we must still reinforce the walls\Nof the damaged blood vessel.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.94,0:00:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.06,0:00:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the proline ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.27,0:00:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.24,0:02:24.20,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(750,0)\pos(360,340)}Downfall
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.67,0:02:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Blood pressure, 128 over 72;\Npulse, 88.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.80,0:02:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems the anesthesia is still working.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.02,0:02:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.02,0:02:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Do your best to survive...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.98,0:02:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...Dr. Boyer!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.73,0:02:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like yours went well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.65,0:03:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. The surgery did...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The mayor died.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.37,0:03:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I-Is that so...?\NThat's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.04,0:03:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Humph! You act as though\Nit's none of your concern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.55,0:03:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the very one\Nwho abandoned our team before surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.22,0:03:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...but, that child\Nwas brought in before the mayor...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.47,0:03:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it matter, who was first?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.06,0:03:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The issue is, because you selfishly\Npulled out of our team,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.14,0:03:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we were forced to fill\Nthe hole you caused!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.69,0:03:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But... Listen to me! I-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.44,0:03:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You upset the teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.78,0:03:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,By order of the Director,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.49,0:03:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I instructed you\Nto perform the surgery on the mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.28,0:03:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But you... You ignored me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.49,0:03:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but, Chief, at that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.50,0:03:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The success of a surgery\Ndepends upon trust
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.63,0:03:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,among the entire staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.84,0:03:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But you made a grand stand play!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.05,0:04:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I have already reported this\Nto the Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.51,0:04:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He greatly regrets this incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.14,0:04:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this has lowered\Nthe prestige of this hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.56,0:04:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.06,0:04:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.44,0:04:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wait a minute!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.44,0:04:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.78,0:04:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,At present, that child's blood pressure\Nis 114 over 82; pulse, 84.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.66,0:04:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,His vitals are very stable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.25,0:04:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...\NThat's good...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.63,0:04:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... That operation...\NIt was wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.18,0:04:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mayor Roddecker, who collapsed\Nwhile on holiday.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.81,0:04:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Has passed away at the hospital.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.39,0:04:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Upon hearing this news,{\i}{\i1}\Npeople have been arriving at the Mayor's office{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.77,0:04:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}with bouquets of flowers,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}many reminiscing on\Nthe life of the Mayor.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.53,0:05:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A press conference has just been held\Nat Eisler Memorial Hospital{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.16,0:05:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}where the Mayor was taken.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.74,0:05:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The cause of\NMayor Roddecker's death{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.04,0:05:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}was due to a cerebral infarction\Nstemming from{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.12,0:05:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}a severe emphraxis\Nof the inner carotid artery{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.62,0:05:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We did everything we could for him,\Nbut it caused severe brain swelling,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.84,0:05:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,which resulted in\Nthis unfortunate outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.05,0:05:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}As for naming a successor,\Na city official explained that{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.22,0:05:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}concrete steps will be taken{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.14,0:05:31.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}-as soon as possible.{\i}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N-I've got to get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.06,0:05:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In the case of the murder of\NMr. and Mrs. Liebert last night...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.48,0:05:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Judging from the signs of\Na search in the rooms,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.06,0:05:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}police believe\Nthis may have been a robbery...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Or perhaps the act of\Na political terrorist{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.44,0:05:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}against this couple\Nwho had fled here from their country{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.78,0:05:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A two-pronged investigation\Nis under way{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.53,0:05:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Of this couple's twin children, the son,{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.66,0:05:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}who received a gunshot wound\Nto the head{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.54,0:05:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}underwent successful surgery but...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.21,0:06:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}has still to regain consciousness.\NHe is listed in critical condition.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.21,0:06:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now, for the weather...{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.34,0:06:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The whole country is{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.55,0:06:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}-in for clear weather...{\i}\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N-That boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.72,0:06:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what will happen to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.51,0:06:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just like him...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.72,0:06:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Reinhardt in ICU\Nis complaining that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.14,0:06:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,she just can't sleep..
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.52,0:06:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we give her something\Nto help her sleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma, are you listening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.07,0:06:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.03,0:06:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh...in that case,\Ngive her one Halcyon tablet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.46,0:06:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Man. He's been in a haze\Nall day long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.13,0:06:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yo!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.05,0:06:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Becker...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.47,0:06:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems you've had a trying time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.26,0:06:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Has the Director\Nhanded down his judgment?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.10,0:06:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I warned you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:07:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you the hospital\Nis ruled by politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.11,0:07:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you played your cards right,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.02,0:07:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,your future would have been\Nsmooth sailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.20,0:07:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well! I guess this means you and \NI are in the same boat now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.25,0:07:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, don't be so depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.50,0:07:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll get a chance\Nto redeem your reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.63,0:07:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go have some drinks.\NIt'll cheer you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.05,0:07:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I still need to get a statement\Nfrom the twin girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.14,0:07:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't discuss that with you now,\NDetective!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.56,0:07:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That girl is gone from her room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.77,0:07:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.82,0:07:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She's always\Nslipping out of her room
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.28,0:07:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and wandering through the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.36,0:07:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.62,0:08:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,...me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.09,0:08:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.93,0:08:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Kill me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.39,0:08:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.93,0:08:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Eisler Memorial Hospital has\Nproven to be
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.19,0:08:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the nation's leading medical facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.48,0:08:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That is first and foremost,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.73,0:08:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the result of our being blessed with
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.44,0:08:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,such excellent personnel\Nsuch as you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I am sincerely grateful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.70,0:08:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.74,0:08:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,unfortunately, the Mayor died\Nhere in this hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.37,0:08:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But, as always,\Nwe had done our utmost to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.17,0:08:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The public's evaluation of this hospital\Nhas not changed one bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.38,0:08:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's have a round of applause\Nfor the ones who strived to save the Mayor's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.30,0:08:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Here to Dr. Boyer and Dr. Eisen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.74,0:09:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked at your paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.32,0:09:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you will continue to\Nwork on your research.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.25,0:09:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Director!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.00,0:09:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh... I must apologize\Nfor my actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.64,0:09:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now... What's done is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.81,0:09:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,\NDirector?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.22,0:09:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You did what you thought you should.\NLet's leave it at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Director...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.61,0:09:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.15,0:09:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,let's have a word from\Nthe Head of Neurosurgery!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.07,0:09:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Pardon me... I'm being called up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.74,0:10:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.74,0:10:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.79,0:10:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Here's the newly appointed...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.25,0:10:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Boyer, please...\NPlease come this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.75,0:10:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, what is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.59,0:10:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you wish to remain at this hospital,\Nyou may do so,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.97,0:10:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,but you'd better give up the idea of\Nrising any further as a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.09,0:10:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That would be impossible for\Nsomeone with a flawed character like yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.06,0:10:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll recognize your skill as a surgeon,\Nbut that is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.69,0:10:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You should also give up any ideas of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.65,0:10:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,presenting any papers\Nat future conferences.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.61,0:10:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But, sir... Please listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.61,0:10:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you wish to move\Nto another hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.61,0:10:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no intention of\Nwriting you a recommendation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.62,0:10:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This means it's no use for you\Nto have any ambition.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.33,0:10:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You may consider your path\Nto becoming
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.83,0:10:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the doctor you envisioned closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.18,0:11:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Surgery requires teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.14,0:11:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Only with the help of each\Nand every one of you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.35,0:11:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,can a life be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.45,0:11:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.58,0:11:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva, won't you talk to your father\Nfor me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.58,0:11:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't done anything wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.71,0:11:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I just operated on\Nan emergency case
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.08,0:11:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in the order in which\Nhe was brought in!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.81,0:11:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's...your engagement ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.56,0:11:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You're such a fool...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.60,0:11:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.82,0:12:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.24,0:12:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, Dr. Norden,\Ndon't you look elegant?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.91,0:12:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As do you! You're more beautiful\Nthan ever tonight, Eva.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.57,0:12:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What a laugh, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.49,0:12:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,After coming across\NDirector Heinemann's paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.28,0:12:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here to Germany,\Nand he made me what I am today...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.37,0:12:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose that paper\Nthat I was so impressed by
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.13,0:13:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was probably written for him\Nby someone somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.63,0:13:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that he was using me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.72,0:13:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but I thought,\Nwhen I reached a certain position,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.35,0:13:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I would be able to work on research\Nof my choice to my heart's content.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.02,0:13:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We are scholars, first and foremost.\NIsn't that right?{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.36,0:13:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not right! Saving people's lives\Nis what's most important to a doctor!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.44,0:13:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}After all, people's lives\Naren't created equal.{\i}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.95,0:13:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.95,0:13:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no distinction\Nbetween people's lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.24,0:13:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I am not wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.37,0:13:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You say there's a flaw\Nin my character?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.58,0:13:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.87,0:13:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You call yourself a doctor;\Nbut you're just money hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.63,0:13:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That bastard... That bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.75,0:13:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He's better off dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I have you to thank...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.81,0:13:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You opened my eyes, as a doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.19,0:13:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You must do your best to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.19,0:14:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I threw everything away\Nin order to operate on you...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.65,0:14:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how far I went\Nin order to bring you back to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.68,0:14:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know your name, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.65,0:14:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your name is Anna Liebert,\Nisn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.66,0:14:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, didn't I, Detective?\NIt's too soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.37,0:14:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't anything be done, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.58,0:14:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, she saw her parents\Nbeing shot before her very eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.50,0:15:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,She has no physical wounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.54,0:15:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but extreme trauma seems to have\Nbrought on amnesia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.51,0:15:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you please refrain from
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.13,0:15:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to get a statement from her\Nfor a while?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.63,0:15:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a difficult case, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.43,0:15:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The victim was\Nan East German diplomat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.72,0:15:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't solve this quickly,\Nthe BKA will come.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.89,0:15:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Those guys always come
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.23,0:15:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and steal the thunder from\Nus state police!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.82,0:15:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't got the time to take it slow.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... What if we do this?\NWe let her see her brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.24,0:15:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She'll be relieved to see him\Nand her memory might return.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot agree on such a gamble–\None suggested by an amateur, at that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.08,0:15:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, Dr. Tenma\Nwill probably not permit it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.08,0:15:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.17,0:15:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the doctor\Nin charge of her brother Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.88,0:15:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsk... What the heck\Nam I supposed to do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.51,0:15:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.52,0:16:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You seem to be in a daze.\NYou look awfully tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.81,0:16:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been so busy\Nwith emergency surgeries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.81,0:16:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They've been working you\Nto the bone...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.32,0:16:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,ever since you were\Ndemoted from Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.78,0:16:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind.\NIt actually makes me feel better.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.20,0:16:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, now... Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.75,0:16:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, I've just been paged.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.33,0:16:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're so tired,\Nbut you still have work to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.25,0:16:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The more diligent you are,\Nthe worse it'll be for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.55,0:16:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this, Director Heinemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.63,0:16:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,See all the gifts\Nand letters of encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.97,0:16:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There are mountains of them\Nin his sister's room, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.56,0:16:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,After losing their parents\Nthese two only have each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.02,0:16:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The mass media keeps reporting on\Ntheir heartbreaking plight,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.98,0:16:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.86,0:16:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as this hospital is concerned,\Nthey're nothing but an inconvenience;
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.53,0:16:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what with no sign of anyone paying\Ntheir medical expenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.36,0:16:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.49,0:16:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So their story is a pitiful one–\Nthat's just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.12,0:16:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.16,0:17:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That means this hospital is\Ngarnering attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.41,0:17:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,For that reason alone,\Nthese kids are valuable...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.42,0:17:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.92,0:17:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.71,0:17:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we do this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.84,0:17:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll give the media\Na photo of the siblings together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.43,0:17:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the media keeps asking\Nfor something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.97,0:17:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it. It'll be a picture\Nof the orphaned siblings
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.69,0:17:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,trying their best to live\Nwithin the warmhearted care
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.81,0:17:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,of our hospital's staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.65,0:17:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But the boy's doctor says\Nit is still too early
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.24,0:17:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to allow them to see each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.95,0:17:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's on his case?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.03,0:17:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.95,0:17:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Dismiss him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.70,0:17:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no need to give that man\Na position that gets so much attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.96,0:17:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Take Dr. Tenma off the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.88,0:17:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.67,0:17:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a heartwarming gift\Nfrom the citizens.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.18,0:17:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you have one?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.10,0:18:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.31,0:18:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel, Mrs. Hankel?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.73,0:18:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, I feel quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Your stitches will be removed soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.62,0:18:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so it won't be long\Nuntil you're released.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.24,0:18:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be able to go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.83,0:18:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but as I said, you must rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.04,0:18:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.29,0:18:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Give Mrs. Hankel regular doses
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.25,0:18:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of an anticonvulsant\Nand a hypotensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.34,0:18:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.81,0:18:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.60,0:18:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.14,0:18:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,They let her see her brother.\NThen she gave a loud scream and...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.23,0:18:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you bring them together?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.49,0:19:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.87,0:19:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Take her back to her room, quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.12,0:19:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.66,0:19:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Boyer, what is the meaning of this?\NWhy the camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.21,0:19:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... We're going to give the media
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.30,0:19:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a picture of the emotional meeting\Nof the two children.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.92,0:19:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Who allowed you to do such a thing?\NI am the boy's doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.43,0:19:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been dismissed\Nas Johan's doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.39,0:19:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.89,0:19:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As of today, he is my patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.02,0:19:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided that it would be fine\Nto let them see each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.61,0:19:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Those children...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.94,0:19:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make those children fodder\Nfor the media!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.11,0:19:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it by order of the Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.53,0:19:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it would be best for you\Nnot to fight it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm the one who saved this boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.49,0:19:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a duty to protect him\Nuntil he is completely healed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.20,0:19:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's the case,\Ntake a look at the boy's reaction!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.51,0:20:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as he saw his sister,\Nhe extended his hand and started crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.93,0:20:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He regained consciousness\Nand showed a normal reaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.02,0:20:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That means the surgery\Nwas a great success.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.64,0:20:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job. Your work is done now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.02,0:20:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Get back to where you belong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.58,0:20:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it...\NDon't make me laugh!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.00,0:20:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares what the Director says?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.09,0:20:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares what the Chief says?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.55,0:20:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all money and power hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.97,0:20:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn them...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.02,0:20:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I'm not wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.67,0:21:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home, Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.42,0:21:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Father? Are you in your room?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.64,0:21:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief...?\NAre you still in a meeting at this hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:21:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, are you asleep?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.33,0:21:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm coming in.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.65,0:22:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That bastard... He's better off dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.03,0:23:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,"For the Love of Life"\NDavid Sylvian - Kuniaki Haishima\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N
